reviewText: Love the combo! Both 20th Century Fox hits in the mid 60's

I am enjoying seeing Hello Dolly again and Star for the first time.  It is a pleasure to view these films without violence, and other annoying expressions of human nature.  These DVDs provide simple pleasure and fun.
I love" Hello Dolly"! Amazing movie and this set had great picture and sound quality. I had never seen "Star" before but I enjoyed it. Both movies are great musicals and instant classics.
the movie is wonderful and i love it no more is needed to be said great movie thank you very much.

This is the second one I have purchased. The first one i ordered i did not realize that it was from Europe. Needless to say it did not play.
So I bought this one. About a quarter of the way through the picture started freezing. I thought it was my DVD unit so I bought a cleaner and that didn't work either. I have put many DVD's in since then and they work just fine. I guess I'm not destined to have this movie.
Two great movies, with two great stars!  I only wish they made this package on Blu Ray!  Loved experiencing these movies again for the first time in years.
Two wonderful movies received in great shape. Thanks for the great service. It provided an around the world watch of the movie "Hello Dolly".

"Hello, Dolly" is one of my favorite Streisand films.  I just LOVE "Love is only Love" and her version of "Hello, Dolly." A young Tommy Tune and Michael Crawford as Ambrose and Cornelius are also a delightful surprise. And Julie Andrews is ALWAYS a delight! She may be one of the most talented singers who has ever lived!
